  "text": "Moreover, for d ≥ 2, the monodromy φ n,d is obtained from φ n,2 by composition with 6d − 12 right handed Dehn twists around the curves a and b. So, by the naturality of the contact invariant under maps induced by Stein cobordisms [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , c + (ξ n,d ) satisfies Condition R as long as c + (ξ n,2 ) does.",
